The fdisk command is a text-based utility for viewing and managing hard disk partitions on Linux.
1. List partition
2. Entering command mode
3. Using command mode
4. Viewing partition table
5. Deleting partition table
6. Creating a partition
7. System ID 
8. Writing changes
9. Formating the partition

------------------

sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda1    # this will list partition details of /dev/sda1 disk device name


